sec.p:
Many tools exist that trim alignments based on low-quality sites
  (Capella-Gutierrez
  et al., 2009;
  Criscuolo
  & Gribaldo, 2010;
  Dress
  et al., 2008;
  Kück
  et al., 2010;
  Penn
  et al., 2010;
  Talavera
  & Castresana, 2007;
  Wu
  et al., 2012). These methods process MSAs on a column-by-column
  basis and can identify alignment blocks where many samples are
  problematic but may not have the power to identify errors affecting
  only one or few of the samples.

list-item.p:
Calculate genetic distances among samples in each window;
      distances can optionally be scaled by distance derived from a
      guide tree.
